  "prompt": "What are the various Incarnations of Lord Vishnu and what is going to be the last Incarnation of Lord Vishnu?",
  "response": "In Hindu mythology, Lord Vishnu is believed to incarnate on Earth in various forms, known as avatars, to restore cosmic order and protect dharma (righteousness). The traditional list of Vishnu's incarnations, as described in texts like the Puranas, includes ten primary avatars known as the **Dashavatara**. Here is the list of these avatars:\n\n1. **Matsya Avatar**: The fish avatar, who saved the first man (Manu) and all species of life from a great deluge.\n2. **Kurma Avatar**: The tortoise avatar, who supported the churning of the ocean (Samudra Manthan) to obtain the nectar of immortality.\n3. **Varaha Avatar**: The boar avatar, who rescued the Earth (represented as the goddess Bhudevi) from the demon Hiranyaksha.\n4. **Narasimha Avatar**: The half-man, half-lion avatar, who defeated the demon Hiranyakashipu to protect his devotee Prahlada.\n5. **Vamana Avatar**: The dwarf avatar, who subdued the demon king Bali by taking three steps to reclaim the universe.\n6. **Parashurama Avatar**: The warrior with an axe, who rid the Earth of corrupt and tyrannical Kshatriya rulers.\n7. **Rama Avatar**: The prince of Ayodhya and hero of the epic Ramayana, who defeated the demon king Ravana.\n8. **Krishna Avatar**: The divine statesman and teacher, who played a pivotal role in the Mahabharata and delivered the Bhagavad Gita.\n9. **Buddha Avatar**: Often identified as Gautama Buddha, who taught the path of compassion and non-violence.\n10. **Kalki Avatar**: The future avatar, who is prophesied to appear at the end of the current age (Kali Yuga) to destroy evil and restore righteousness.\n\n### The Last Incarnation: **Kalki Avatar**\nKalki is believed to be the final incarnation of Lord Vishnu, who is yet to appear. According to Hindu eschatology, Kalki will arrive at the end of **Kali Yuga** (the current age of darkness and moral decline). Riding a white horse and wielding a blazing sword, Kalki will destroy the forces of evil, restore dharma, and usher in a new golden age called Satya Yuga.\n\nThe Kalki Avatar is described in various Puranas, including the **Vishnu Purana** and **Bhagavata Purana**, and is prophesied to appear when the world is in chaos and suffering. His arrival symbolizes the renewal of cosmic order and the beginning of a new era of peace and righteousness.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
